{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"The story starts in Kenya"},{"time":3000,"text":"in December of 2007,"},{"time":5000,"text":"when there was a disputed presidential election,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and in the immediate aftermath of that election,"},{"time":10000,"text":"there was an outbreak of ethnic violence."},{"time":12000,"text":"And there was a lawyer in Nairobi, Ory Okolloh --"},{"time":15000,"text":"who some of you may know from her TEDTalk --"},{"time":17000,"text":"who began blogging about it on her site,"},{"time":19000,"text":"Kenyan Pundit."},{"time":21000,"text":"And shortly after the election and the outbreak of violence,"},{"time":24000,"text":"the government suddenly imposed"},{"time":26000,"text":"a significant media blackout."},{"time":28000,"text":"And so weblogs went from being"},{"time":30000,"text":"commentary as part of the media landscape"},{"time":32000,"text":"to being a critical part of the media landscape"},{"time":35000,"text":"in trying to understand where the violence was."},{"time":38000,"text":"And Okolloh solicited"},{"time":40000,"text":"from her commenters"},{"time":42000,"text":"more information about what was going on."},{"time":44000,"text":"The comments began pouring in,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and Okolloh would collate them. She would post them."},{"time":48000,"text":"And she quickly said, \"It's too much."},{"time":50000,"text":"I could do this all day every day"},{"time":52000,"text":"and I can't keep up."},{"time":54000,"text":"There is more information"},{"time":56000,"text":"about what's going on in Kenya right now"},{"time":58000,"text":"than any one person can manage."},{"time":60000,"text":"If only there was a way to automate this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"And two programmers who read her blog"},{"time":64000,"text":"held their hands up and said, \"We could do that,\""},{"time":67000,"text":"and in 72 hours, they launched Ushahidi."},{"time":70000,"text":"Ushahidi -- the name means \"witness\""},{"time":72000,"text":"or \"testimony\" in Swahili --"},{"time":74000,"text":"is a very simple way of taking reports from the field,"},{"time":77000,"text":"whether it's from the web or, critically,"},{"time":80000,"text":"via mobile phones and SMS,"},{"time":82000,"text":"aggregating it and putting it on a map."},{"time":85000,"text":"That's all it is, but that's all that's needed"},{"time":87000,"text":"because what it does is it takes the tacit information"},{"time":90000,"text":"available to the whole population --"},{"time":92000,"text":"everybody knows where the violence is,"},{"time":94000,"text":"but no one person knows what everyone knows --"},{"time":97000,"text":"and it takes that tacit information"},{"time":99000,"text":"and it aggregates it,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and it maps it and it makes it public."},{"time":103000,"text":"And that, that maneuver"},{"time":105000,"text":"called \"crisis mapping,\""},{"time":107000,"text":"was kicked off in Kenya"},{"time":110000,"text":"in January of 2008."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"And enough people looked at it and found it valuable enough"},{"time":115000,"text":"that the programmers who created Ushahidi"},{"time":117000,"text":"decided they were going to make it open source"},{"time":119000,"text":"and turn it into a platform."},{"time":121000,"text":"It's since been deployed in Mexico"},{"time":123000,"text":"to track electoral fraud."},{"time":125000,"text":"It's been deployed in Washington D.C. to track snow cleanup."},{"time":128000,"text":"And it's been used most famously in Haiti"},{"time":130000,"text":"in the aftermath of the earthquake."},{"time":133000,"text":"And when you look at the map"},{"time":135000,"text":"now posted on the Ushahidi front page,"},{"time":137000,"text":"you can see that the number of deployments in Ushahidi"},{"time":139000,"text":"has gone worldwide, all right?"},{"time":142000,"text":"This went from a single idea"},{"time":144000,"text":"and a single implementation"},{"time":146000,"text":"in East Africa in the beginning of 2008"},{"time":149000,"text":"to a global deployment"},{"time":151000,"text":"in less than three years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"Now what Okolloh did"},{"time":157000,"text":"would not have been possible"},{"time":159000,"text":"without digital technology."},{"time":162000,"text":"What Okolloh did would not have been possible"},{"time":165000,"text":"without human generosity."},{"time":167000,"text":"And the interesting moment now,"},{"time":169000,"text":"the number of environments"},{"time":171000,"text":"where the social design challenge"},{"time":173000,"text":"relies on both of those things being true."},{"time":176000,"text":"That is the resource that I'm talking about."},{"time":179000,"text":"I call it cognitive surplus."},{"time":181000,"text":"And it represents the ability"},{"time":183000,"text":"of the world's population"},{"time":185000,"text":"to volunteer and to contribute and collaborate"},{"time":188000,"text":"on large, sometimes global, projects."},{"time":191000,"text":"Cognitive surplus is made up of two things."},{"time":193000,"text":"The first, obviously, is the world's free time and talents."},{"time":196000,"text":"The world has over"},{"time":198000,"text":"a trillion hours a year"},{"time":201000,"text":"of free time"},{"time":203000,"text":"to commit to shared projects."},{"time":205000,"text":"Now, that free time existed in the 20th century,"},{"time":207000,"text":"but we didn't get Ushahidi in the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"That's the second half of cognitive surplus."},{"time":212000,"text":"The media landscape in the 20th century"},{"time":214000,"text":"was very good at helping people consume,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and we got, as a result,"},{"time":219000,"text":"very good at consuming."},{"time":221000,"text":"But now that we've been given media tools --"},{"time":223000,"text":"the Internet, mobile phones -- that let us do more than consume,"},{"time":226000,"text":"what we're seeing is that people weren't couch potatoes"},{"time":229000,"text":"because we liked to be."},{"time":231000,"text":"We were couch potatoes because that was"},{"time":233000,"text":"the only opportunity given to us."},{"time":235000,"text":"We still like to consume, of course."},{"time":237000,"text":"But it turns out we also like to create,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and we like to share."},{"time":242000,"text":"And it's those two things together --"},{"time":244000,"text":"ancient human motivation"},{"time":246000,"text":"and the modern tools to allow that motivation"},{"time":248000,"text":"to be joined up in large-scale efforts --"},{"time":251000,"text":"that are the new design resource."},{"time":254000,"text":"And using cognitive surplus,"},{"time":256000,"text":"we're starting to see truly incredible experiments"},{"time":259000,"text":"in scientific, literary,"},{"time":261000,"text":"artistic, political efforts."},{"time":264000,"text":"Designing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"We're also getting, of course, a lot of LOLcats."},{"time":269000,"text":"LOLcats are cute pictures of cats"},{"time":271000,"text":"made cuter with the addition of cute captions."},{"time":274000,"text":"And they are also"},{"time":276000,"text":"part of the abundant media landscape we're getting now."},{"time":279000,"text":"This is one of the participatory --"},{"time":281000,"text":"one of the participatory models"},{"time":283000,"text":"we see coming out of that, along with Ushahidi."},{"time":286000,"text":"Now I want to stipulate, as the lawyers say,"},{"time":288000,"text":"that LOLcats are the stupidest possible"},{"time":290000,"text":"creative act."},{"time":292000,"text":"There are other candidates of course,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but LOLcats will do as a general case."},{"time":297000,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":299000,"text":"The stupidest possible creative act"},{"time":301000,"text":"is still a creative act."},{"time":304000,"text":"Someone who has done something like this,"},{"time":307000,"text":"however mediocre and throwaway,"},{"time":310000,"text":"has tried something, has put something forward in public."},{"time":313000,"text":"And once they've done it, they can do it again,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and they could work on getting it better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"There is a spectrum between mediocre work and good work,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and as anybody who's worked as an artist or a creator knows,"},{"time":324000,"text":"it's a spectrum you're constantly"},{"time":326000,"text":"struggling to get on top of."},{"time":328000,"text":"The gap is between"},{"time":330000,"text":"doing anything and doing nothing."},{"time":333000,"text":"And someone who makes a LOLcat"},{"time":335000,"text":"has already crossed over that gap."},{"time":338000,"text":"Now it's tempting to want to get the Ushahidis"},{"time":340000,"text":"without the LOLcats, right,"},{"time":342000,"text":"to get the serious stuff without the throwaway stuff."},{"time":345000,"text":"But media abundance never works that way."},{"time":348000,"text":"Freedom to experiment means freedom to experiment with anything."},{"time":351000,"text":"Even with the sacred printing press,"},{"time":353000,"text":"we got erotic novels 150 years"},{"time":355000,"text":"before we got scientific journals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"So before I talk about"},{"time":362000,"text":"what is, I think, the critical difference"},{"time":364000,"text":"between LOLcats and Ushahidi,"},{"time":366000,"text":"I want to talk about"},{"time":368000,"text":"their shared source."},{"time":370000,"text":"And that source is design for generosity."},{"time":373000,"text":"It is one of the curiosities of our historical era"},{"time":376000,"text":"that even as cognitive surplus"},{"time":378000,"text":"is becoming a resource we can design around,"},{"time":380000,"text":"social sciences are also starting to explain"},{"time":383000,"text":"how important"},{"time":385000,"text":"our intrinsic motivations are to us,"},{"time":387000,"text":"how much we do things because we like to do them"},{"time":390000,"text":"rather than because our boss told us to do them,"},{"time":392000,"text":"or because we're being paid to do them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"This is a graph from a paper"},{"time":398000,"text":"by Uri Gneezy and Aldo Rustichini,"},{"time":400000,"text":"who set out to test, at the beginning of this decade,"},{"time":403000,"text":"what they called \"deterrence theory.\""},{"time":405000,"text":"And deterrence theory is a very simple theory of human behavior:"},{"time":407000,"text":"If you want somebody to do less of something,"},{"time":409000,"text":"add a punishment and they'll do less of it."},{"time":411000,"text":"Simple, straightforward, commonsensical --"},{"time":414000,"text":"also, largely untested."},{"time":416000,"text":"And so they went and studied"},{"time":418000,"text":"10 daycare centers in Haifa, Israel."},{"time":420000,"text":"They studied those daycare centers"},{"time":422000,"text":"at the time of highest tension,"},{"time":424000,"text":"which is pick-up time."},{"time":426000,"text":"At pick-up time the teachers,"},{"time":428000,"text":"who have been with your children all day,"},{"time":430000,"text":"would like you to be there at the appointed hour to take your children back."},{"time":433000,"text":"Meanwhile, the parents -- perhaps a little busy at work, running late, running errands --"},{"time":436000,"text":"want a little slack to pick the kids up late."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439000,"text":"So Gneezy and Rustichini said,"},{"time":441000,"text":"\"How many instances of late pick-ups"},{"time":443000,"text":"are there at these 10 daycare centers?\""},{"time":445000,"text":"Now they saw -- and this is what the graph is,"},{"time":447000,"text":"these are the number of weeks and these are the number of late arrivals --"},{"time":450000,"text":"that there were between six and 10"},{"time":452000,"text":"instances of late pick-ups"},{"time":454000,"text":"on average in these 10 daycare centers."},{"time":456000,"text":"So they divided the daycare centers into two groups."},{"time":459000,"text":"The white group there"},{"time":461000,"text":"is the control group; they change nothing."},{"time":464000,"text":"But the group of daycare centers represented by the black line,"},{"time":467000,"text":"they said, \"We are changing this bargain"},{"time":469000,"text":"as of right now."},{"time":471000,"text":"If you pick your kid up more than 10 minutes late,"},{"time":473000,"text":"we're going to add a 10 shekel fine to your bill."},{"time":475000,"text":"Boom. No ifs, ands or buts.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"And the minute they did that,"},{"time":480000,"text":"the behavior in those daycare centers changed."},{"time":482000,"text":"Late pick-ups went up"},{"time":484000,"text":"every week for the next four weeks"},{"time":487000,"text":"until they topped out at triple the pre-fine average,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and then they fluctuated"},{"time":492000,"text":"at between double and triple the pre-fine average"},{"time":494000,"text":"for the life of the fine."},{"time":496000,"text":"And you can see immediately what happened, right?"},{"time":500000,"text":"The fine broke the culture"},{"time":502000,"text":"of the daycare center."},{"time":504000,"text":"By adding a fine,"},{"time":506000,"text":"what they did was communicate to the parents"},{"time":508000,"text":"that their entire debt to the teachers"},{"time":510000,"text":"had been discharged"},{"time":512000,"text":"with the payment of 10 shekels,"},{"time":514000,"text":"and that there was no residue of guilt or social concern"},{"time":517000,"text":"that the parents owed the teachers."},{"time":519000,"text":"And so the parents, quite sensibly, said,"},{"time":521000,"text":"\"10 shekels to pick my kid up late?"},{"time":523000,"text":"What could be bad?\""},{"time":525000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"The explanation of human behavior"},{"time":531000,"text":"that we inherited in the 20th century"},{"time":534000,"text":"was that we are all rational, self-maximizing actors,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and in that explanation --"},{"time":539000,"text":"the daycare center had no contract --"},{"time":542000,"text":"should have been operating without any constraints."},{"time":545000,"text":"But that's not right."},{"time":547000,"text":"They were operating with social constraints"},{"time":549000,"text":"rather than contractual ones."},{"time":551000,"text":"And critically, the social constraints"},{"time":553000,"text":"created a culture that was more generous"},{"time":556000,"text":"than the contractual constraints did."},{"time":558000,"text":"So Gneezy and Rustichini run this experiment for a dozen weeks --"},{"time":561000,"text":"run the fine for a dozen weeks --"},{"time":563000,"text":"and then they say, \"Okay, that's it. All done; fine.\""},{"time":566000,"text":"And then a really interesting thing happens:"},{"time":568000,"text":"Nothing changes."},{"time":571000,"text":"The culture that got broken by the fine"},{"time":574000,"text":"stayed broken when the fine was removed."},{"time":577000,"text":"Not only are economic motivations"},{"time":580000,"text":"and intrinsic motivations"},{"time":582000,"text":"incompatible,"},{"time":584000,"text":"that incompatibility"},{"time":586000,"text":"can persist over long periods."},{"time":589000,"text":"So the trick"},{"time":591000,"text":"in designing these kinds of situations"},{"time":593000,"text":"is to understand where you're relying on"},{"time":596000,"text":"the economic part of the bargain -- as with the parents paying the teachers --"},{"time":599000,"text":"and when you're relying on the social part of the bargain,"},{"time":602000,"text":"when you're really designing for generosity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"This brings me back to the LOLcats"},{"time":608000,"text":"and to Ushahidi."},{"time":610000,"text":"This is, I think, the range that matters."},{"time":612000,"text":"Both of these rely on cognitive surplus."},{"time":614000,"text":"Both of these design for the assumption"},{"time":616000,"text":"that people like to create and we want to share."},{"time":619000,"text":"Here is the critical difference between these:"},{"time":624000,"text":"LOLcats is communal value."},{"time":627000,"text":"It's value created by the participants"},{"time":629000,"text":"for each other."},{"time":631000,"text":"Communal value on the networks we have"},{"time":634000,"text":"is everywhere --"},{"time":636000,"text":"every time you see a large aggregate"},{"time":638000,"text":"of shared, publicly available data,"},{"time":641000,"text":"whether it's photos on Flickr"},{"time":643000,"text":"or videos on Youtube or whatever."},{"time":645000,"text":"This is good. I like LOLcats as much as the next guy,"},{"time":647000,"text":"maybe a little more even,"},{"time":649000,"text":"but this is also"},{"time":652000,"text":"a largely solved problem."},{"time":654000,"text":"I have a hard time envisioning a future"},{"time":656000,"text":"in which someone is saying,"},{"time":658000,"text":"\"Where, oh where, can I find a picture"},{"time":660000,"text":"of a cute cat?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"Ushahidi, by contrast,"},{"time":664000,"text":"is civic value."},{"time":666000,"text":"It's value created by the participants"},{"time":668000,"text":"but enjoyed by society as a whole."},{"time":670000,"text":"The goals set out by Ushahidi"},{"time":672000,"text":"are not just to make life better"},{"time":674000,"text":"for the participants,"},{"time":676000,"text":"but to make life better for everyone in the society"},{"time":679000,"text":"in which Ushahidi is operating."},{"time":681000,"text":"And that kind of civic value"},{"time":684000,"text":"is not just a side effect"},{"time":686000,"text":"of opening up to human motivation."},{"time":689000,"text":"It really is going to be a side effect"},{"time":691000,"text":"of what we, collectively,"},{"time":693000,"text":"make of these kinds of efforts."},{"time":696000,"text":"There are a trillion"},{"time":698000,"text":"hours a year"},{"time":700000,"text":"of participatory value"},{"time":702000,"text":"up for grabs."},{"time":704000,"text":"That will be true year-in and year-out."},{"time":707000,"text":"The number of people who are going to be able"},{"time":709000,"text":"to participate in these kinds of projects"},{"time":711000,"text":"is going to grow,"},{"time":713000,"text":"and we can see that organizations"},{"time":716000,"text":"designed around a culture of generosity"},{"time":718000,"text":"can achieve incredible effects"},{"time":720000,"text":"without an enormous amount of contractual overhead --"},{"time":723000,"text":"a very different model"},{"time":725000,"text":"than our default model for large-scale group action in the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"What's going to make the difference here"},{"time":732000,"text":"is what Dean Kamen said,"},{"time":735000,"text":"the inventor and entrepreneur."},{"time":737000,"text":"Kamen said, \"Free cultures get what they celebrate.\""},{"time":741000,"text":"We've got a choice before us."},{"time":744000,"text":"We've got this trillion hours a year."},{"time":746000,"text":"We can use it to crack each other up, and we're going to do that."},{"time":749000,"text":"That, we get for free."},{"time":751000,"text":"But we can also celebrate"},{"time":753000,"text":"and support and reward the people"},{"time":755000,"text":"trying to use cognitive surplus"},{"time":757000,"text":"to create civic value."},{"time":759000,"text":"And to the degree we're going to do that, to the degree we're able to do that,"},{"time":762000,"text":"we'll be able to change society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}